###<a name="about">About</a>

pepper is a flexible statistics generator for source code management
software. It can be used to create graphical or textual reports of code
repositories, independent from the actual SCM software used.  It comes
with several built-in reports, but custom reports can be easily written
using the [Lua](http://www.lua.org) scripting language. A basic Lua
interface to [Gnuplot](http://www.gnuplot.info) is provided and can be
used to plot repository data graphically.

Please see the [[Gallery]] page for a quick look on output images
generated by some of pepper's built-in reports.

pepper is free and open-source software. Currently, the
program is in a very early stage of development, so it
can be considered alpha software. Feature suggestions,
bug reports as well as report and code contributions [are
welcome](https://sourceforge.net/tracker/?group_id=386093)!


####Feature overview:

* Custom report scripts can be written in [Lua](http://www.lua.org)
* Support for multiple repository types. As of version 0.1,
  [Git](http://ww.git-scm.com), [Subversion](http://subversion.apache.org)
  and [Mercurial](http://mercurial.selenic.com/) are supported
* [Gnuplot](http://www.gnuplot.info) interface for report scripts
* Fast local diffstat and meta-data cache using zlib compression

